question: What is the average number of number of movies added to the lists of user 8516503? Indicate how many movies did he/she give a rating score of 5.
pred_sql:
SELECT 
    AVG(l.list_movie_number) AS avg_movies,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ratings WHERE user_id = 8516503 AND rating_score = 5) AS five_star_count
FROM lists_users lu
JOIN lists l ON lu.list_id = l.list_id
WHERE lu.user_id = 8516503;
gt_sql: SELECT AVG(T3.list_movie_number) , SUM(CASE WHEN T1.rating_score = 5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM ratings AS T1 INNER JOIN lists_users AS T2 ON T1.user_id = T2.user_id INNER JOIN lists AS T3 ON T2.user_id = T3.user_id WHERE T1.user_id = 8516503

question: List all employees working for publisher 'GGG&G'. State their name and job description.
pred_sql:
SELECT CONCAT(e.fname, ' ', e.minit, ' ', e.lname) AS employee_name, j.job_desc 
FROM employee e 
JOIN jobs j ON e.job_id = j.job_id 
JOIN publishers p ON e.pub_id = p.pub_id 
WHERE p.pub_name = 'GGG&G';

question: What was the total price of the products shipped to Rovelli Gifts Distributors Ltd. between 1/1/2003 and 12/31/2003?

FROM customers c
JOIN orders o ON c.customerNumber = o.customerNumber
JOIN orderdetails od ON o.orderNumber = od.orderNumber
WHERE c.customerName = 'Rovelli Gifts Distributors Ltd.'
AND DATE(o.orderDate) BETWEEN '2003-01-01' AND '2003-12-31';

question: Among the customers who have ordered the product "Telescoping Adjustable Floor Lamp", how many of them are consumers?
pred_sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.[Customer ID]) AS Consumer_Count
FROM (
  SELECT [Customer ID] FROM central_superstore
  UNION ALL
  SELECT [Customer ID] FROM east_superstore
  UNION ALL
  SELECT [Customer ID] FROM south_superstore
  UNION ALL
  SELECT [Customer ID] FROM west_superstore
) AS AllOrders
JOIN product AS prod ON AllOrders.[Customer ID] = prod.[Product ID]
JOIN people AS p ON AllOrders.[Customer ID] = p.[Customer ID]
WHERE prod.[Product Name] = 'Telescoping Adjustable Floor Lamp'
AND p.Segment = 'Consumer';
gt_sql: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.`Customer Name`) FROM people AS T1 INNER JOIN central_superstore AS T2 ON T1.`Customer ID` = T2.`Customer ID` INNER JOIN product AS T3 ON T3.`Product ID` = T2.`Product ID` WHERE T3.`Product Name` = 'Telescoping Adjustable Floor Lamp' AND T1.Segment = 'Consumer'

question: Of all the nonessential genes that are not of the motorprotein class and whose phenotype is cell cycle defects, how many do not have a physical type of interaction?
pred_sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT G.GeneID) 
FROM Genes G 
LEFT JOIN Interactions I 
ON G.GeneID = I.GeneID1 
WHERE G.Essential = 'No' 
AND G.Class != 'Motor protein' 
AND G.Phenotype = 'cell cycle defects' 
AND I.Type != 'physical' OR I.Type IS NULL;
gt_sql: SELECT COUNT(T1.GeneID) FROM Genes AS T1 INNER JOIN Interactions AS T2 ON T1.GeneID = T2.GeneID1 WHERE T2.Type != 'Physical' AND T1.Phenotype = 'Cell cycle defects' AND T1.Class != 'Motorproteins' AND T1.Essential = 'Non-Essential'

question: What percentage of donations are given via a giving or campaign page? List the primary area of those donations.
pred_sql:
SELECT 
    pf.primary_focus_area,
    ROUND(
        (SUM(CASE WHEN d.via_giving_page = 't' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) / 
        (SUM(CASE WHEN d.via_giving_page = 't' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + 
         SUM(CASE WHEN d.via_giving_page != 't' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END))) * 100, 2
    ) AS percentage_donations_via_giving_page
FROM donations d
LEFT JOIN projects p ON d.projectid = p.projectid
LEFT JOIN projects pf ON p.projectid = pf.projectid
GROUP BY pf.primary_focus_area;
gt_sql: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.via_giving_page = 't' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(donation_total), ( SELECT T2.primary_focus_area FROM donations AS T1 INNER JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.projectid = T2.projectid WHERE T1.via_giving_page = 't' GROUP BY T2.primary_focus_area ORDER BY SUM(T1.donation_total) DESC LIMIT 1 ) result FROM donations AS T1 INNER JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.projectid = T2.projectid

question: How many games were sold on PS3 platform in Japan?
pred_sql:
SELECT SUM(rs.num_sales) AS total_sales
FROM region_sales rs
INNER JOIN region r ON rs.region_id = r.id
INNER JOIN game_platform gp ON rs.game_platform_id = gp.id
INNER JOIN platform p ON gp.platform_id = p.id
WHERE p.platform_name = 'PS3' AND r.region_name = 'Japan';
gt_sql: SELECT SUM(T1.num_sales * 100000) FROM region_sales AS T1 INNER JOIN region AS T2 ON T1.region_id = T2.id INNER JOIN game_platform AS T3 ON T1.game_platform_id = T3.id INNER JOIN platform AS T4 ON T3.platform_id = T4.id WHERE T2.region_name = 'Japan' AND T4.platform_name = 'PS3'

question: How many times does the Catalan word "nombre" repeat itself?
pred_sql: SELECT SUM(lw.occurrences) AS total_occurrences FROM langs_words lw INNER JOIN langs l ON lw.lid = l.lid INNER JOIN words w ON lw.wid = w.wid WHERE l.lang = 'Catalan' AND w.word = 'nombre';
gt_sql: SELECT T1.occurrences FROM langs_words AS T1 INNER JOIN words AS T2 ON T1.wid = T2.wid WHERE T2.word = 'nombre'

question: Which airline does the aircraft with the fastest flight belong to?
pred_sql:
SELECT AC.Description FROM Airlines A
JOIN 'Air Carriers' AC ON A.OP_CARRIER_AIRLINE_ID = AC.Code
WHERE A.ACTUAL_ELAPSED_TIME = (SELECT MIN(A.ACTUAL_ELAPSED_TIME) FROM Airlines A)
LIMIT 1;
gt_sql: SELECT T1.OP_CARRIER_AIRLINE_ID FROM Airlines AS T1 INNER JOIN Airports AS T2 ON T1.ORIGIN = T2.Code WHERE T1.ACTUAL_ELAPSED_TIME IS NOT NULL AND T1.CRS_ELAPSED_TIME IS NOT NULL ORDER BY T1.ACTUAL_ELAPSED_TIME - T1.CRS_ELAPSED_TIME ASC LIMIT 1

question: Had Bitcoin's price increased or decreased on 2013/5/5 compared with the price 7 days before?
